                     <unittitle label="Title:">
                        <title render="doublequote">Ode On the Pleasure arising from
									Vicissitude</title>
                     </unittitle>
                     <unitdate normal="1780" certainty="circa">1780[?]</unitdate>
                     <physdesc>
                        <extent unit="pages">11</extent>
                        <physfacet>transcript in an unidentified neat and legible hand on
									Whatman paper</physfacet>
                        <dimensions>180 mm x 110 mm</dimensions>
                     </physdesc>
                     <physloc label="Identifier:">
								MS Add. 439, <title render="doublequote">Fragments</title> section, 
								7-17
							</physloc>
                     <physloc label="Building:">The Archives</physloc>
                     <repository>YMAR</repository>
                     <note>
                        <p>MS catalogued by <persname normal="Huber, Alexander">Alexander 
									Huber</persname> in The Archives, York Minster Library &amp; Archives, on <date normal="20070327">27/03/2007</date>.</p>
                     </note>
                  </did>
                  <scopecontent>
                     <p>Transcript in an unidentified neat and legible hand, entitled <title render="doublequote">Ode On the Pleasure arising from
								Vicissitude</title>	(p. 7) (<title render="doublequote">Ode. II.</title>
								[p. 9]). The poem, which is annotated "N.B. This Ode was left
								unfinished by M<emph render="super">r</emph>. Gray; but was compleated
								by M<emph render="super">r</emph>. Mason. // The lines by M<emph render="super">r</emph>. Mason are marked * / single words _" and
								is identical to the version in <extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/resources/glnames.shtml#Mason, William, 1724-1797"
                                show="replace">
                           <persname normal="Mason, William, 1724-1797">Mason</persname>'s</extref>
                        <title render="italic">Poems</title> (<date normal="1775" type="publication">1775</date>), <extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/cgi-bin/view.cgi?collection=primary&amp;edition=1775&amp;part=2&amp;text=oopv"
                                show="replace">78-81</extref>, is
								part of a section called <title render="doublequote">Fragments</title>, which is 
								separately paginated and has its own table of contents (p. 19), in a
								volume entitled <title render="italic">Gray's Poems</title>. The book
								carries the bookplate of <persname normal="Gray, Thomas, 1716-1771" source="lcnaf">Gray</persname>'s friend and biographer <persname normal="Mason, William, 1724-1797">William Mason</persname>.
							</p>
                  </scopecontent>
